26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_fb_rammcp77.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#define mcp77_ram(p) container_of((p), struct mcp77_ram, base)
30#include "ram.h"
31
32struct mcp77_ram {
33 struct nvkm_ram base;
34 u64 poller_base;
35};
36
37static int
38mcp77_ram_init(struct nvkm_ram *base)
39{
40 struct mcp77_ram *ram = mcp77_ram(base);
41 struct nvkm_device *device = ram->base.fb->subdev.device;
42 u32 dniso = ((ram->base.size - (ram->poller_base + 0x00)) >> 5) - 1;
43 u32 hostnb = ((ram->base.size - (ram->poller_base + 0x20)) >> 5) - 1;
44 u32 flush = ((ram->base.size - (ram->poller_base + 0x40)) >> 5) - 1;
45
46 /* Enable NISO poller for various clients and set their associated
47 * read address, only for MCP77/78 and MCP79/7A. (fd#25701)
48 */
49 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c18, dniso);
50 nvkm_mask(device, 0x100c14, 0x00000000, 0x00000001);
51 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c1c, hostnb);
52 nvkm_mask(device, 0x100c14, 0x00000000, 0x00000002);
53 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c24, flush);
54 nvkm_mask(device, 0x100c14, 0x00000000, 0x00010000);
55 return 0;
56}
57
58static const struct nvkm_ram_func
59mcp77_ram_func = {
60 .init = mcp77_ram_init,
61 .get = nv50_ram_get,
62 .put = nv50_ram_put,
63};
64
65int
66mcp77_ram_new(struct nvkm_fb *fb, struct nvkm_ram **pram)
67{
68 struct nvkm_device *device = fb->subdev.device;
69 u32 rsvd_head = ( 256 * 1024); /* vga memory */
70 u32 rsvd_tail = (1024 * 1024) + 0x1000; /* vbios etc + poller mem */
71 u64 base = (u64)nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100e10) << 12;
72 u64 size = (u64)nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100e14) << 12;
73 struct mcp77_ram *ram;
74 int ret;
75
76 if (!(ram = kzalloc(sizeof(*ram), GFP_KERNEL)))
77 return -ENOMEM;
78 *pram = &ram->base;
79
80 ret = nvkm_ram_ctor(&mcp77_ram_func, fb, NVKM_RAM_TYPE_STOLEN,
81 size, 0, &ram->base);
82 if (ret)
83 return ret;
84
85 ram->poller_base = size - rsvd_tail;
86 ram->base.stolen = base;
87 nvkm_mm_fini(&ram->base.vram);
88
89 return nvkm_mm_init(&ram->base.vram, rsvd_head >> NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT,
90 (size - rsvd_head - rsvd_tail) >>
91 NVKM_RAM_MM_SHIFT, 1);
92}
